Strange rebuild behavior
{noformat}
diff --git a/src/rebuild/initiator.c b/src/rebuild/initiator.c
index 4df87a09..9f342783 100644
--- a/src/rebuild/initiator.c
+++ b/src/rebuild/initiator.c
@@ -792,7 +792,9 @@ rebuild_obj_ult(void *data)
        memset(&anchor, 0, sizeof(anchor));
        memset(&dkey_anchor, 0, sizeof(dkey_anchor));
        memset(&akey_anchor, 0, sizeof(akey_anchor));
-       dc_obj_shard2anchor(&anchor, arg->shard);
+       dc_obj_shard2anchor(&dkey_anchor, arg->shard);
+       daos_anchor_set_flags(&dkey_anchor,
+                             DAOS_ANCHOR_FLAGS_TO_LEADER);
 
        /* Initialize enum_arg for VOS_ITER_DKEY. */
        memset(&enum_arg, 0, sizeof(enum_arg));
{noformat}

With above patch, the master will hung when run "daos_test.sh -i" with 4 servers. Sometimes, it is found that some 2-replicas object may have two shards are both in-rebuilding status:
{noformat}
03/25-02:41:48.45 boro-40 DAOS[15166] placement DBUG src/placement/ring_map.c:1219 obj_layout_dump() dump layout for 72057611217797148.1
03/25-02:41:48.45 boro-40 DAOS[15166] placement DBUG src/placement/ring_map.c:1223 obj_layout_dump() 0: shard_id 0, tgt_id 1, fseq 1, in-rebuilding yes
03/25-02:41:48.45 boro-40 DAOS[15166] placement DBUG src/placement/ring_map.c:1223 obj_layout_dump() 1: shard_id 1, tgt_id 0, fseq 1, in-rebuilding yes
{noformat}

daos_cont.h missing from install/include
After PR-1654 merged for DAOS-2660, I'm encountering the following error when building mpich:


{noformat}
2020/01/03 07:29:34 ERROR 'cd /home/pahender/mpich/build && make -j8' failed (2): In file included from ../../../../src/mpi/romio/adio/ad_daos/ad_daos.h:20:0,                   
                 from ../../../../src/mpi/romio/adio/ad_daos/ad_daos_close.c:14:                                                                                                 
/home/pahender/daos/install/include/daos.h:32:23: fatal error: daos_cont.h: No such file or directory                                                                            
 #include <daos_cont.h>     {noformat}
 

The daos_cont.h file needs to be added to the install/include directory in the src/SConscript.

Clean up the comments and coding style of mgmt dRPC handlers
As [~accountid:60357e9c5ddf020069b1cf90] pointed out, the following comment in the mgmt dRPC handlers could be improved:
{noformat}
/* response status is populated with SUCCESS on init */{noformat}
Also, the coding style, such as the line break below, should be fixed:
{noformat}
        pb_rank = mgmt__daos_rank__unpack(
                NULL, drpc_req->body.len, drpc_req->body.data);
{noformat}
